261.2	Patent_troll	Patent troll	Patent troll is a pejorative term used for a person or company who buys and enforces patents against one or more alleged infringers in a manner considered by the target or observers as unduly aggressive or opportunistic, often with no intention to further develop, manufacture or market the patented invention.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/53/Woodward_light_bulb.JPG/220px-Woodward_light_bulb.JPG
